  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink7-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> ituvumatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink7">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> yaṟanaṉi ciṟakka vallatu keṭuka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> yuḷaippū marutattuk kiḷaikkuru kirukkun</l>
          <l> taṇṭuṟai yūraṉ ṟaṉṉūrk </l>
          <l> koṇṭaṉaṉ celka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May Dharma greatly prevail! Down with Non[-Dharma]!' </l>
<l>          That's what our mother wants. As for us: </l>
<l>          'The man from the village by the cool ghat</l>
<l  rend="indent2">          where egrets perch on the branches of the Myrobalan tree with its feathery flowers: </l>
<l>          May he go as one who takes me to his village!' — that's what we have been wanting.</l>
          
          


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
